  "prompt": "Google Nexus 7: How to change default action for playing video from Engadget app? I have chosen YouTube but it doesn't play. My HTC One X uses streaming media player. How to change this default action to streaming media player?",
  "response": "To change the default action for playing videos from the Engadget app on your Google Nexus 7, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Clear Defaults for the Engadget App**:\n   - Go to **Settings** on your Nexus 7.\n   - Tap on **Apps** or **Applications**.\n   - Scroll and find the **Engadget** app in the list. Tap on it.\n   - In the app details, look for an option called **Clear defaults**. Tap this to reset any previously set default actions for the app.\n\n2. **Try to Open a Video Again**:\n   - Open the Engadget app and try to play a video again. This should prompt you to select which app you'd like to use to play the video.\n\n3. **Select the Streaming Media Player**:\n   - When prompted with the list of available apps to play the video, select your preferred streaming media player (e.g., the default media player on your HTC One X) and choose **Always** if you want to set it as the default for future use.\n\n4. **Setting the Default Application for Videos**:\n   - If you want to ensure that your streaming media player is the default for all video content, you might have to do similar steps for the streaming media player app (clear defaults), and then you will have a chance to re-select it when opening videos.\n\nIf you continue to face issues with it not playing videos in the desired app, you might want to check if there are any restrictions related to the app or if a specific codec is needed for video playback. Additionally, confirm that both the Engadget app and your streaming media player app are updated to their latest versions for optimal compatibility.",
